Quote: <i>Tickle</i>. 2. To steal from, to rob, as in<i> tickle a peter</i>, to rob the till: New Zealand c. (- 1932). Perhaps ex<i> to tickle trout.</i> see <i>sere</i> and <i>tail. </i>
